en altered forever. It had all begun just hours earlier when the 1996 NFL Draft commenced, a day that would change the course of football history. The stage was set, with teams eager to bolster their rosters with fresh talent, and the anticipation was palpable as the draft's first round got underway. As the day unfolded, it became clear that this draft would be one for the books, with a plethora of skilled players waiting to be selected. On April 22, 1996, the NFL Draft was held, and the first overall pick was none other than the highly touted wide receiver Keyshawn Johnson, a player whose impressive college career had made him a household name among football fans. The New York Jets, in dire need of a playmaker, made the pivotal decision to select Johnson, a choice that would have significant implications for their franchise. As the draft progressed, other notable players such as Kevin Hardy, Simeon Rice, and Jonathan Ogden were also selected, each destined to leave their mark on the sport. The immediate aftermath of the draft saw teams and fans alike buzzing with excitement, as the potential of their newly acquired players was weighed and debated. In the years that followed, the 1996 NFL Draft would prove to be a watershed moment, with many of its participants going on to achieve greatness, and Keyshawn Johnson's selection serving as a catalyst for a new era of Jets football. Today, the 1996 NFL Draft remains an important milestone in the annals of football history, a testament to the enduring power of the sport to captivate and inspire audiences, and a reminder of the profound impact that a single day can have on the lives of athletes and the fate of franchises.	Cuando finalmente se disipó el polvo, el panorama del fútbol americano había cambiado para siempre. Todo había comenzado justo horas antes, cuando el draft de la NFL de 1996 estaba a punto de comenzar. La emoción y la expectativa eran palpables, ya que los equipos y los jugadores esperaban saber qué les de